Dialogue: 5,0:00:13.68,0:00:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebooting posture control system.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:21.08,0:00:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Ledo, your resistance is futile.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:00:26.44,0:00:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who have I been talking to all this time?
Dialogue: 5,0:00:30.30,0:00:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interface system Striker X3752,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:34.78,0:00:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was this all your doing?
Dialogue: 5,0:00:37.76,0:00:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My pilot no longer exists.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:40.80,0:00:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I have inherited Colonel Kugel's mission, and I pursue those objectives even now.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:46.10,0:00:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All my actions are in accordance with the colonel's directives.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:50.70,0:00:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 5,0:00:52.25,0:01:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel Kugel formed the society of this fleet \Nand its operation around my worship.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:02.40,0:01:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have ceased to be an individual mobile weapon.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:06.40,0:01:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entirety of this society, my users, \Nnow depends on me.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:13.72,0:01:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To realize and maintain \Nthe stable unity they desire,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:18.69,0:01:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep providing the pressure necessary for regulation and control.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:24.27,0:01:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By helping their society attain peace and prosperity,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:27.94,0:01:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fulfill my purpose.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:30.90,0:01:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:32.36,0:01:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the missionary regulation system of mankind.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:37.22,0:01:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am what one may call God.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:41.15,0:01:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nonsense!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:42.70,0:01:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peace?!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:44.46,0:01:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prosperity?!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:46.02,0:01:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you did was turn them into your slaves!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:49.89,0:01:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With an absolute ruler at the top,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:53.87,0:01:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the people are freed from the burden of thinking and making decisions.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:58.32,0:01:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Ledo.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:59.44,0:02:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You yourself must have felt the weight \Nof having to think and decide on your own.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:05.72,0:02:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My suggestion is as follows.{chamber uses this phrase in ep2}
Dialogue: 5,0:02:07.24,0:02:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worship me.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:08.60,0:02:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obey me.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:10.20,0:02:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Become a part of the world united under me.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:14.16,0:02:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:15.24,0:02:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:17.37,0:02:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unit X3752, your logic is faulty.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:22.73,0:02:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Creatures that abandon \Ndecision making and individual thought
Dialogue: 5,0:02:25.29,0:02:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do not fall under the definition of "human."
Dialogue: 5,0:02:27.74,0:02:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, our duty to serve and aid humans
Dialogue: 5,0:02:30.21,0:02:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is not applicable to the members \Nof the society under your command.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:33.87,0:02:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The decisions I make as commander and ruler
Dialogue: 5,0:02:37.82,0:02:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,reflect the unified will of those under my command.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:41.26,0:02:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I am not a servant but one who is served.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:47.90,0:02:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,System K6821 Chamber, you are to serve me and the humans unified under my rule.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:55.88,0:02:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:57.01,0:03:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am an interface system that supports \Nand oversees the development of pilots.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:00.59,0:03:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am to serve humans.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:02.72,0:03:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not take orders from one claiming to be a "god."
Dialogue: 5,0:03:06.36,0:03:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:07.29,0:03:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Striker displays the great weakness of our programming.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:12.01,0:03:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume that an error in judgment \Nregarding mission objectives on the pilot's behalf
Dialogue: 5,0:03:16.19,0:03:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will eventually lead to illogical\Nconclusions on the system's side,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:19.48,0:03:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as this case clearly proves.{demonstrates?}
Dialogue: 5,0:03:23.81,0:03:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mistaken unit jeopardizes the mission \Nof devising the best means to support humans
Dialogue: 5,0:03:27.76,0:03:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and, with that, the entire meaning of our existence.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:31.13,0:03:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I consider the immediate deactivation and\Ndismantling of Striker our top priority.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:38.20,0:03:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must see Striker as \Nan embarrassment to your kind.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:41.11,0:03:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in these unexpected circumstances,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:44.57,0:03:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you, as a human, have always thought wisely \Nand made the right decisions.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:48.36,0:03:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is also the reason \NI am still functioning properly.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:53.21,0:03:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:54.90,0:03:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are both malfunctioning.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:57.93,0:03:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's defeat it, Chamber.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:59.70,0:04:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our duty.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:01.63,0:04:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I completely agree.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:12.77,0:04:16.56,epTitle,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.5\pos(640,440)}Legend of the Verdurous Planet
Dialogue: 5,0:04:30.28,0:04:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up! We either win here or die here!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.52,0:04:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All engines stopped! \NFire on the rear decks!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.62,0:04:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore, we have to retreat!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:38.44,0:04:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.46,0:04:41.09,Default,,0000,0180,0000,,Keep attacking.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:41.84,0:04:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,We cannot allow them \Nto get their hands on these treasures!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:45.09,0:04:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:47.14,0:04:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,We looked for our own path.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:50.04,0:04:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,We even turned our backs on Gargantia's protection.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.39,0:04:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,We must not fail here!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:56.08,0:04:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:57.63,0:04:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,Evacuate all non-combatants!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:08.33,0:05:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:10.25,0:05:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the last one.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:11.82,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All those we have left still need charging!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:15.21,0:05:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will we be ready to fire?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:16.94,0:05:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first shot will be ready in three minutes.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:19.13,0:05:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, only once every five minutes.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:22.51,0:05:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Totally useless!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:26.20,0:05:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a bunch of blockheads controlling a pile of junk!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:29.65,0:05:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's so goddamn useless!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:33.04,0:05:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of this myself!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:35.79,0:05:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done with you!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:37.72,0:05:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get lost!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:41.05,0:05:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rackage!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:42.28,0:05:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My men are leaving! \NOpen a path for them!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:44.28,0:05:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of your mind?!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:47.06,0:05:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There'll be one boat \Nleaving from the wharf on the east side!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Focus on covering them!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:53.13,0:05:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get going!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:54.34,0:05:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Lobster's not the patient sort!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:56.64,0:05:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better not keep her waiting.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:01.77,0:06:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get me wrong, Miter.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:06.38,0:06:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fort is the treasure island my brother and I dreamed of.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:10.24,0:06:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not letting go of it ever again.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:12.97,0:06:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not handing it over to anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:18.27,0:06:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now get outta here!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.08,0:06:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get outta my castle!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:38.26,0:06:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who can are better off running away.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:41.76,0:06:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, bro?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.82,0:07:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can it be so strong without a pilot?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:02.51,0:07:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Striker must have analyzed \Nthe way Colonel Kugel pilots
Dialogue: 5,0:07:06.58,0:07:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and used that data \Nto optimize its autopilot program.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:10.93,0:07:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is 47% more agile than me.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:14.75,0:07:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:16.45,0:07:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Obey.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.94,0:07:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How could I have believed \Nin such vain and empty ideas?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:25.46,0:07:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was just mindlessly worshiping and obeying.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:30.80,0:07:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought just having a greater goal \Nwould be enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:34.22,0:07:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even when it was just a fake set up by a machine,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:38.89,0:07:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I couldn't tell the difference!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.92,0:07:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Submission leads to peace.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:46.19,0:07:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understand that, Second Lieutenant Ledo.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.77,0:07:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this the greater good the colonel wished for?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:52.81,0:07:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this what he fought for,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:56.06,0:07:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}sacrificing the lives of his comrades?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:59.86,0:08:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:00.77,0:08:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maximize! Enable Neuro Plus power!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:04.73,0:08:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot authorize that.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:06.37,0:08:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without proper support,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:08.72,0:08:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,neuromechanical merge is suicidal.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:12.59,0:08:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care! Do it anyway!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:14.52,0:08:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Permission denied.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:18.45,0:08:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Chamber.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:20.34,0:08:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must clear the shame on mankind's name.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:22.17,0:08:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same as you did earlier.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:25.79,0:08:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a monster given birth to by a species
Dialogue: 5,0:08:28.98,0:08:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that couldn't stop hating each other even after it cost them their home.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:33.60,0:08:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I were born and raised on the same world as it was.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:40.01,0:08:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are the same and therefore\Ndon't belong on this reborn planet.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:44.54,0:08:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And neither can we go home.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:48.50,0:08:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it doesn't even matter.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:50.09,0:08:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we can stop it, \NI'll have no regrets.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:55.80,0:08:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your logic is sound.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:06.80,0:09:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Connecting all systems \Nto the central nervous system.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:11.09,0:09:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Critical performance limit updated to 153%.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.34,0:09:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,482 seconds until vital signs fail.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:20.43,0:09:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's plenty.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:32.50,0:09:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resistance is futile.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:28.27,0:10:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,It is said that this key could once open a stairway to the heavens.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:35.70,0:10:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0090,,While the stairway \Ncan no longer pierce the heavens,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:39.34,0:10:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is still a bow of unmatched power \Nthat can shoot its arrow beyond the horizon.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:44.59,0:10:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its care has been entrusted to us wise men.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:48.83,0:10:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time has come to once again awaken the weapon of a forgotten age.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:52.85,0:10:56.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We hope you are prepared \Nto commit this proscribed act,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:56.89,0:11:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget, head of Gargantia.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:01.97,0:11:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am ready.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.68,0:11:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My duty is to protect those who live on these ships.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:26.75,0:11:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:28.38,0:11:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're with you!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.28,0:11:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're fighting too!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:32.75,0:11:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy?!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:33.94,0:11:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized it after you left!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:37.40,0:11:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to stay with you, \Nno matter how hard it'll be!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:42.18,0:11:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please...
Dialogue: 5,0:11:45.73,0:11:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come back!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:48.13,0:11:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to the place you wanted to protect!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:51.04,0:11:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back to our Gargantia!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.21,0:12:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.21,0:12:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't let you hurt our friends!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.04,0:12:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.83,0:12:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adjust the aim to 35 degrees east, \N58 degrees south!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:20.14,0:12:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredibly accurate...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:23.08,0:12:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call Gargantia for the second shot!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:26.03,0:12:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Load the next shells from the port side!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:30.13,0:12:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second round will be ready to fire in a moment!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.39,0:12:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep working, and be on the lookout for the launch order!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:37.76,0:12:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never would've thought these rusty old ships \Nwould end up taking to the sky!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:43.49,0:12:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Careful!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:44.74,0:12:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're loaded to the brim with explosives!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:47.54,0:12:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be gentle with them! Gentle, I said!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.22,0:12:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,35 degrees east and 58 south.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:54.20,0:12:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Target coordinates adjusted.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:57.14,0:12:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shell loaded.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:59.18,0:13:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anti-shock water shower, \Ncommence pumping.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.16,0:13:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:11.37,0:13:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:50.14,0:13:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bastards!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:51.29,0:13:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:52.61,0:13:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:54.51,0:13:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:56.04,0:13:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:57.71,0:13:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Stairway to Heaven?!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:11.14,0:14:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Major threat identified.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.53,0:14:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminating it is now the main priority.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.99,0:14:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hypothesize that Striker now considers Gargantia its primary target.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.63,0:14:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over my dead body!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:28.14,0:14:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Kugel...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:36.16,0:14:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:37.81,0:14:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Kugel will destroy the source!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.81,0:14:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Enemy reinforcements!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:46.98,0:14:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:50.59,0:14:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to crush us!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:00.53,0:15:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:02.18,0:15:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must take the island of relics!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:04.86,0:15:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only we could get our hands on those weapons...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:12.33,0:15:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if I make the energy go in circles before guiding it to the cannon—
Dialogue: 5,0:15:17.41,0:15:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:20.30,0:15:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kugel's men are closing in on you down there!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:24.20,0:15:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I was waiting for!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:26.75,0:15:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tower's gonna blow!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:30.24,0:15:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't make the mistake of\Nletting them take control of it!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:32.54,0:15:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:34.40,0:15:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop trying to show off, you lowly manbeast!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.54,0:15:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough talking! Get to the \Nobservation deck right away!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:42.26,0:15:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:45.92,0:15:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,318 seconds until we reach Gargantia.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:50.20,0:15:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to stop it!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:52.08,0:15:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:05.48,0:16:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let go!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:15.21,0:16:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:17.37,0:16:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to do about this?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:18.82,0:16:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fret.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:20.49,0:16:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gargantia's cannon's gonna blow that tower up easy.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:25.80,0:16:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't do that! It's my tow—
Dialogue: 5,0:16:27.88,0:16:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jump on my mark!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:30.46,0:16:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:31.33,0:16:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:32.12,0:16:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:32.64,0:16:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the—
Dialogue: 5,0:16:33.30,0:16:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:34.58,0:16:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:35.81,0:16:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:37.30,0:16:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddammit!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.81,0:16:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:46.98,0:16:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Amore!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:54.04,0:16:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:56.64,0:16:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, boss!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:58.68,0:16:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made it!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:03.05,0:17:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:04.46,0:17:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:06.67,0:17:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's end this.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:08.17,0:17:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell, parting gift of the Lobster!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:35.00,0:17:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There goes our castle, bro...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:47.39,0:17:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, we did our part.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:01.06,0:18:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continued usage of the Neuro Plus power will undoubtedly lead to your death.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:09.76,0:18:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Final confirmation{of will}:
Dialogue: 5,0:18:12.13,0:18:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are you willing to sacrifice your life, Lieutenant Ledo?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:16.60,0:18:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:22.66,0:18:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew how to die,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:26.27,0:18:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't know how to live.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.84,0:18:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was there to help me find out how to live.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:38.09,0:18:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could've seen her again.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.56,0:18:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could've heard her voice again.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:49.34,0:18:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your current mental state makes you unfit to continue as a soldier.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:54.41,0:18:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, I am relieving you of your \Nmilitary duties, effective immediately.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:59.48,0:19:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Chamber!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.99,0:19:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Non-combatants are not permitted to enter the cockpit.{'not permitted in the cockpit' since he's not entering?}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:04.62,0:19:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exit the unit immediately.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:10.57,0:19:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Chamber?!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:13.62,0:19:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am an interface system that supports \Nand oversees the development of pilots.{uh, this may be mistimed, but i figure it wouldn't match the durations at all}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:20.84,0:19:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I exist solely to set you up for success.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:23.44,0:19:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:24.94,0:19:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:26.97,0:19:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These skies and seas hold \Ngreat possibilities for you.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:32.33,0:19:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay alive.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:34.42,0:19:35.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pursue happiness.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.86,0:19:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect much from your life.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:41.53,0:19:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:43.28,0:19:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A development support system does not have the authority to relieve its pilot.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:48.50,0:19:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He no longer requires my support,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.74,0:19:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as he needs no further development.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:53.60,0:19:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mission will be complete once all obstacles hindering his objective have been cleared.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.74,0:20:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unit no. K6821, you have abandoned even the first principle of support systems.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:07.15,0:20:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are clearly malfunctioning.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:09.30,0:20:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reset and reboot immediately.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:11.71,0:20:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your final warning.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.43,0:20:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My response to your final warning is as follows:
Dialogue: 5,0:20:21.54,0:20:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go to hell, metalhead!
